1 AN ACT proposing to create a new section of the Constitution of Kentucky relating
2 to property exempt from taxation.
3 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
4 Section 1. Are you in favor of providing an additional property tax exemption
5 on the permanent residence of an owner who is veteran, first responder, or the surviving
6 spouse of a veteran or first responder by amending the Constitution of Kentucky to read
7 as stated below?
8 SECTION 2. IT IS PROPOSED THAT A NEW SECTION BE ADDED TO
9 THE CONSTITUTION OF KENTUCKY TO READ AS FOLLOWS:
10 (1) There shall be exempt from taxation:
11 (a) Forty percent of the assessed valuation of real property maintained as the
12 permanent residence of the owner who is a veteran of the Armed Forces of the United
13 States and has a one hundred percent service-connected disability adjudicated by the
14 United States Department of Veterans Affairs or its successor;
15 (b) Thirty percent of the assessed valuation of real property maintained as the
16 permanent residence of the owner who served as a first responder in the
17 Commonwealth and is classified as totally disabled as a result of an injury received
18 while in active service or training as a first responder;
19 (c) Twenty percent of the assessed valuation of real property maintained as the
20 permanent residence of the owner who is a veteran with ten or more years of service in
21 the Armed Forces of the United States; and
22 (d) Ten percent of the assessed valuation of real property maintained as the
23 permanent residence of the owner who served as a first responder in the
24 Commonwealth for ten or more years.
25 (2) To qualify for an exemption under this section based on the owner's
26 disability status, the owner shall satisfy the disability requirements and stipulations
27 mandated under Section 170 of this Constitution.
