1 (3) Real property maintained as the permanent residence of the surviving
2 spouse of a veteran or first responder who qualified for an exemption under this
3 section prior to his or her death may continue to receive the exemption based on the
4 qualifiers of the veteran or first responder as long as the surviving spouse does not
5 remarry.
6 (4) The General Assembly may by law specify the qualifications necessary for
7 an individual to be considered a veteran, first responder, or surviving spouse for
8 purposes of the exemptions provided in this section.
9 (5) Real property shall not receive more than one exemption under this section,
10 but may receive an exemption under Section 170 of this Constitution if the property
11 qualifies.
12 (6) The exemptions in this section are provided notwithstanding contrary
13 provisions of Sections 171, 172, and 174 of this Constitution.
14 Section 3. This amendment shall be submitted to the voters of the
15 Commonwealth for their ratification or rejection at the time and in the manner provided
16 for under Sections 256 and 257 of the Constitution, KRS 118.415, and under Sections 4
17 and 5 of this Act.
18 Section 4. Notwithstanding any provision of KRS 118.415 to the contrary, the
19 Secretary of State shall cause the question in Section 1 of this Act and the entirety of the
20 proposed amendment to the Constitution of Kentucky contained in Section 2 of this Act
21 to be published at least one time in a newspaper of general circulation published in this
22 state, and shall also cause to be published at the same time and in the same manner the
23 fact that the amendment will be submitted to the voters for their acceptance or rejection at
24 the next regular election at which members of the General Assembly are to be voted for.
25 The publication required by this section and KRS 118.415 shall be made no later than the
26 first Tuesday in August preceding the election at which the amendment is to be voted on.
27 Section 5. Notwithstanding any provision of KRS 118.415 to the contrary, not
